main event: 2/Lt. Leland M. Martin, while on a routine mission, sighted two meteor-like objects of yellowish-red color passing in front of the aircraft at altitudes of 10,000 and 8,000 feet, respectively.
interesting points: The first object was observed at 10,000 feet and the second at approximately 8,000 feet., Both objects were described as similar to the afterburner of an F-102., The objects were moving in an East-West direction., No unknown aircraft were reported in the area during the sightings., The crew speculated that the objects might have been rockets from a nearby gunnery range.
witness description: 2/Lt. Leland M. Martin, copilot, 964th Squadron of 552nd AEW&Con Wing.
